# AndroidAgent
An on-device AI agent for Android — voice-driven memo application powered by LLM intent extraction.

## Project Status
Work in progress — v0.1 (Voice recording → LLM parsing → structured memo output)

## Roadmap
- **v0.1**: Voice memo recording, cloud LLM for speech content intent extraction
- **v0.2**: On-device quantized Qwen2.5 LLM, native integration with system memo & calendar
- **v0.3**: Cross-app intelligent agent via Accessibility Service, Android Intent and MCP protocol

## Tech Stack
Kotlin, Jetpack Compose, Room Database, OkHttp, Qwen LLM API

## Quick Start
1. Clone repository
```bash
git clone git@github.com:everydaytobehappy/AndroidAgent.git
```
2. Open the project in Android Studio and sync Gradle dependencies
3. Fill your Qwen API Key in the config file to launch the app

## Core Features
1. Real-time voice recording & speech-to-text conversion
2. LLM automatic content analysis: auto classify notes into to-dos, schedules, random notes and reminders
3. Structured memo storage with category tags & search capability, persisted locally
4. Future offline version: fully local on-device LLM without cloud transmission for better privacy protection